February 5, 2017 2:51 pm Updated: February 5, 2017 6:10 pm Heavy police presence outside apartment building in Elmwood By Shelden Rogers Reporter Global News 
Police have closed a section of Midwinter Avenue in front of an apartment building. Chris Stanton/Global News What is this?

WINNIPEG – A number of police vehicles were stationed outside an apartment building on Midwinter Avenue. 
Global News cameras have captured three woman escorted out of the building by officers, and put into police cruisers. 
RELATED: Cab driver injured in early morning shooting in Elmwood: Unicity 
Midwinter Avenue was closed to traffic at Levis Street, while police remained on scene. 
Winnipeg police did not answer any calls for information on what happened, but did post on twitter, that they were on scene of a serious incident. Police are investigating a serious incident on Midwinter Ave. Midwinter is closed between Brazier and Levi St. 
— Winnipeg Police (@wpgpolice) February 5, 2017 © 2017 Global News, a division of Corus Entertainment Inc.
